N:opencontext
D:Project/repo memory and cross-agent handoff using OpenContext. Use when an agent needs durable context across sessions, searchable decisions/lessons, manifests or stable links for what to read next, or a load→search→store workflow for active delivery work. Route long-lived narrative knowledge bases to llm-wiki, structural repo mapping to graphify, and human-authored vault organization to note/vault skills.
G:opencontext context-management memory project-memory multi-agent handoff stable-links manifests
U[5]:
  When repo or project context must survive across sessions
  When decisions, pitfalls, or acceptance notes should be searchable later
  When another agent needs a compact handoff packet or reading manifest
  When OpenContext setup, MCP integration, or stable links are the actual task
  When the user is deciding between OpenContext, a wiki, a graph layer, or a note vault